HEADWORD: Petrography
<hw>Pe*trog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Petro</ets> + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
art of writing on stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The scientific description of rocks; that department
of science which investigates the constitution of rocks;
petrology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>petrohyoid</ent>⟦br⟧
